From: Pavel Begunkov <asml.silence@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] udp/ipv6 optimisations v2 net-next
Date: Thu Jan 27 00:36:31 2022 +0000

UPSTREAM STATUS: Merged in Linux 5.18
  Reference: https://lore.kernel.org/all/cover.1643243772.git.asml.silence@gmail.com/
  This patch is NOT applied on kernels >= 5.18.

Squashed series of UDP/IPv6 sendmsg optimisations:
  - Partially inline ipv6_fixup_options to avoid overhead when opt is NULL
  - Optimise dst refcounting on cork init (save two atomics)
  - Avoid extra copies of iflow in udpv6_sendmsg
  - Pass flow in ip6_make_skb together with cork
  - Convert inet_cork argument to inet_cork_full in __ip6_append_data
  - Don't zero inet_cork_full::fl after use (saves 88-byte memset)
  - Remove daddr temp buffer in __ip6_make_skb
  - Optimise dst refcounting on skb init

Signed-off-by: Pavel Begunkov <asml.silence@gmail.com>
---
NOTE: This patch file is kept for reference only. The changes are
already present in Linux 6.x. Do not apply to 6.x kernels.
